      <memberdef kind="function" id="namespacehelios_1_1core_1_1types_1abddc1987e78cb80aba95ce8f6e73af7e" prot="public" static="no" nodiscard="yes" constexpr="yes" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" noexcept="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t helios::core::types::fnv1a_hash</definition>
        <argsstring>(const std::string_view str) noexcept</argsstring>
        <name>fnv1a_hash</name>
        <qualifiedname>helios::core::types::fnv1a_hash</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>const std::string_view</type>
          <declname>str</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Computes a 32-bit FNV-1a hash from a string. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Implements the Fowler–Noll–Vo hash function (FNV-1a variant), a fast, non-cryptographic hash suitable for hash tables and identifier generation. The function is `constexpr`, enabling compile-time hashing of string literals.</para>
<para>## Algorithm</para>
<para>1. Initialize hash with FNV offset basis (2166136261) 2. For each byte: XOR with hash, then multiply by FNV prime (16777619)</para>
<para>## Usage</para>
<para>```cpp // Compile-time hash for type-safe IDs constexpr uint32_t id = fnv1a_hash(&quot;enemy_spawn&quot;);</para>
<para>// Used internally by strongly-typed ID constructors constexpr GameObjectPoolId POOL{&quot;bullets&quot;}; // calls fnv1a_hash ```</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>str</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The string view to hash.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>32-bit hash value.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This is not a cryptographic hash. Do not use for security purposes.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fowler%E2%80%93Noll%E2%80%93Vo_hash_function">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fowler%E2%80%93Noll%E2%80%93Vo_hash_function</ulink> </para>
</simplesect>
